The paper deals with the problem of consensus in shared memory, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. The paper specifically focuses on the special case of anonymous processes, where all processes run the same algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are the two most relevant categories for distributed computing research. The paper also involves lower bounds and complexity analysis, which are typical topics in theoretical computer science. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.IT (Information Theory), which are relevant categories for complexity theory and lower bounds.
